1780420455844040	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyuRI		item.create	bn-1lj2	{"description":"Found 2026-06-02 dogfooding pre.2 (merging bn-sdv4/bn-3ej6/bn-16x2 on the\nconsolidated maw repo). After `maw ws merge`, the repo root had an\nUNTRACKED, NON-gitignored `.manifold/events/merge.jsonl` containing\n`integration_started` events for the merged workspaces — while the correct,\nlayout-aware oplog `.maw/manifold/events/merge.jsonl` ALSO got them.\n\nSo a merge integration-event emitter resolves the legacy `.manifold/` base\npath (relative to root/cwd) instead of the consolidated `.maw/manifold/`\nlocation. The canonical oplog is correct and complete, so this is duplicate\n(mis-routed) writes, not data loss.\n\nIMPACT (minor but real):\n- Litters the consolidated repo root with a stray `.manifold/` dir.\n- It is NOT gitignored, so it shows up as untracked and risks being\n  accidentally `git add`-ed / committed.\n- Indicates a layout-unaware path resolution in the merge event code that\n  should use the same LayoutFlavor-aware base-path resolution as the main\n  oplog.\n\nREPRO: on a consolidated repo, `maw ws merge <ws> --into default --destroy`,\nthen `git status` → `?? .manifold/` with events/merge.jsonl.\n\nFIX: route the integration-event emitter through the layout-aware manifold\nbase path (.maw/manifold/ in consolidated, .manifold/ in v2) so it writes to\nthe same place as the canonical oplog. Grep for the merge.jsonl /\nintegration_started emitter and the base-path it uses. Add a test asserting\nno `.manifold/` is created at root after a merge in a consolidated repo.\n","kind":"bug","labels":["layout","v1-0"],"size":"s","title":"ws merge writes integration events to legacy root .manifold/ in consolidated layout (should be .maw/manifold/)"}	blake3:EyA65C7IK7lHEqVZ8W79Asq3DUrPWT6mGGGMkTcX6Jk
